article.headline: UC Riverside 69, SE Missouri State 61
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Davis Misko scored a career-high 22 points and Rickey Porter made six free throws in the final 35 seconds as UC Riverside beat Southeast Missouri State 69-61 Saturday. Porter added 11 points for UC Riverside (4-19), and Misko also led the Highlanders with seven rebounds. Roy Booker had a game-high 23 points for Southeast Missouri (6-19), and Terrick Willoughby added 16. Waylon Francis had a game-high nine rebounds for the Redhawks. The Highlanders led by as many as 22 in the second half, but let the Redhawks back into the game with four turnovers in six possessions with just over five minutes to play. An Eric Jones three-point play brought Southeast Missouri to within single digits, 58-49, with 4:54 to go. Willoughby made a 3-pointer to bring Southeast Missouri within four 63-59 with 45 seconds left, and the Redhawks fouled to stop the clock. Porter made a pair of free throws, Booker answered with two free throws, then Porter made four straight to secure the win.
